  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the industrial sector for sustainable livelihoods in the Syrian Arab Republic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at maintaining and improving industrial vocational and technical trainings across Syria as a tool to accelerate the re-establishment of sustainable livelihoods among local communities. The project will (i) support the refurbishing of selected training departments of Syrian Vocational Training centers; (ii) train vocational and technical instructors; (iii) support micro-, small- and medium-sized enterprises (MSMEs) by proving access for technical training for their workers; and (iv) introduce STEM curricula at primary schools located among some of the communities most affected by the conflict.

This project will be implemented within the framework of a partnership project titled &#x201C;Building human capacity for the future generations in Syria&#x201D; output 4: economic governance and capacity of the productive sectors enhanced. The project is also in line with the 2018 Humanitarian Response Plan - Early Recovery and Livelihoods sector strategy and its defining humanitarian principles. The project is also aligned with the interventions under the UNSF 2016-2019 Focus Area 3 &#x201C;improving socio-economic resilience of the Syrian people&#x201D; - outcome 3 &#x201C;households and communities benefit from sustainable livelihoods opportunities, including economic recovery and social inclusion&#x201D; and its output 3.1 &#x201C;Income, sustainable livelihood opportunities and inclusive local economic development are restored and maintained&#x201D; and output 3.2 &#x201C;Social and economic needs of the most vulnerable are identified and addressed&#x201D;.</narrative>
  </description>
